Package ru.nsu.ablaginin

Class Tree<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • ru.nsu.ablaginin.Tree<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<Tree<T>>
    public class Tree<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<Tree<T>>
    Tree is a hierarchical data structure. If we have some vertex V and vertex U, then we can define the relations for each element of the tree: - parent(U) = V - V is a U's parent - children(V) = [U] - get all the V's children Description of the construction of Tree: - root is a Tree; - T is a Tree, (V (- T) and not (U (- T) if T' is such that parent(U) = V and (T'\U = T), then T' is a Tree

      • delete

        public T delete()
        The function removes the vertex from the tree. Vertex's children is added to the parent's children. Call `( 2 ).remove`: ( 0 ) ( 0 ) / | \ -----\ / / \ \ ( 1 ) (-2-) ( 3 ) -----/ ( 1 ) ( 5 ) ( 6 ) ( 3 ) / / \ / ( 4 ) ( 5 ) ( 6 ) ( 4 ) So, ( 0 ) has 4 children now. Warning: deleting the root is forbidden!
        Returns:
        value of the deleted branch
